commit.message: Explicitly set end on stdin to false when not set to false
Explicitly set stream end=false when not set to true.
Add kwarg 'end' to the send input function which will allow the stdin pipe to be closed to the remote process.
Change send std input function doc by a single word.
Change default encoding for input sent to running processes.
Modify how unicode is handled for python2 to allow both byte arrays and unicode strings.
Remove todo since @jborean93 is positive that there is no more error checking that is needed.
Cast test strings to unicode for unit testing on python2
Make changes to input function to allow proper unicode encoding for python2.
Remove comments related sending std input to running process.
Fix unit tests for sending input
Add a single test for sending input to stdin
Add a function to send input to a running process.
